ABOUT THE PLACE
Poznan is the capital of the Wielkopolska Province which is the cradle of the
 Polish nation. Situated halfway between Warsaw and Berlin, the town is a
 significant center of industry, science, culture and commerce. Poznaq is
 among the biggest academic centers in Poland. The city is known for its
 cultural institutions like drama theatres, Philharmonic Hall with a famous boys'
 choir,  the Opera House and many museums. The Cathedral, which has its
 roots 10 centuries ago, houses the tombs of Poland's first kings. On the Old
 Market Square one can admire the Renaissance Town Hall, acclaimed as one
 of the most beautiful town halls in Central Europe. There are many interesting
 castles, palaces and  archeological sites to be visited in the immediate vicinity
 of Poznan .

The Conference and Training Center "Zeglarz" is located in Kiekrz, 10 km 
 from the city centre of Poznaq. This  famous touristic area, with large forest,
 fresh air, a brillant lake and silence, creats an unforgettable microclimate.
 "Zeglarz" is well prepared to host conferences. Its main room contains 200
 comfortable chairs and hotel rooms are fully furnished, each with WC, a
 shower and TV set. Meals are served in the hotel restaurant. 

