CANCELLATION AND REFUNDS
Written requests for cancellation and refund of registration fees should be
 addressed to the Conference Secretariat.  A deduction of DM 150  for
 administrative costs will be made for cancellations received before 5 October
 1993. 50% will be deducted for cancellations received before 20 October
 1993 and after 5 October 1993. No refund can be made for any cancellation
 received after that date.

ACCOMMODATION
Accomodation and full board are included in the conference fee. Participants
 will be accomodated in private rooms in the "Zeglarz" Hotel. Each room has
 its own bathroom with WC and shower and is equipped with TV. The meals
 will be served in the "Zeglarz" restaurant. For those who  come by car a
 secure parking place will be provided. 

TRANSPORTATION
Poznaq is accessible by various means of transportation. The city has its local
 airport with several international flights. There are also daily local air
 connections with Warszawa (Warsaw), the capital of Poland and the main
 airport of the country.  Poznan can be accessed from all main cities of Poland 
 by express train  connections or by highways. It is linked by Inter City trains
 with Berlin and Paris. From Scandinavia, one of possible ways is to come by
 ferry to Gdansk or Swinoujscie and then by train to Poznan. From Germany
 the city can be easily accessed by car.
On 26 and 27 October there will be some local arrangements at the Poznan
 airport and central railway station to help delegates to get to the conference
 site.
Detailed transportation information will be send after registration.


CONFERENCE DINNER

The cost of the Conference Dinner is covered by the registration fee. It will
 take place outside the city of Poznan. It is planned to have a concert of a
 famous boys' choir called "Nightingales of Poznan" an open air
barbecue is considered for the night of October 27th.
"  after the dinner.

ACCOMPANYING PERSONS
Because of a limited capacity of the "Zeglarz" hotel only one accompanying
 person per participant can be accomodated provided he/she will share the
